The paper deals with distributed optimization in networked systems, which involves communication, information theory, and machine learning. The use of gossip communication and the focus on network topology suggest that the paper may belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.IT (Information Theory). The use of convex optimization and machine learning techniques suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Finally, the use of distributed algorithms and network topology suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
